. display as text ""


. display as text "  The Barro-Sala-i-Martin (1992) convergence equation:"
  The Barro-Sala-i-Martin (1992) convergence equation:

. display as text ""


. display as text "    (1/s) × ln(y_{t+s}/y_t) = α - ((1 - exp(-β×s))/s) × ln(y
> _t) + ε"
    (1/s) × ln(y_{t+s}/y_t) = α - ((1 - exp(-β×s))/s) × ln(y_t) + ε

. display as text ""


. display as text "  Breaking down each term:"
  Breaking down each term:

. display as text "    Left side:  annualized growth rate over s years"
    Left side:  annualized growth rate over s years

. display as text "    α:          intercept (related to the steady-state incom
> e)"
    α:          intercept (related to the steady-state income)

. display as text "    β:          speed of convergence (fraction of gap closed
>  per year)"
    β:          speed of convergence (fraction of gap closed per year)

. display as text "    s:          number of years between initial and final pe
> riod"
    s:          number of years between initial and final period

. display as text "    ln(y_t):    log of initial GDP per capita"
    ln(y_t):    log of initial GDP per capita

. display as text "    ε:          error term (random shocks to growth)"
    ε:          error term (random shocks to growth)

. display as text ""


. display as text "  The key expression is: (1 - exp(-β×s))/s"
  The key expression is: (1 - exp(-β×s))/s

. display as text "    This is the 'convergence factor' — how much of the initi
> al"
    This is the 'convergence factor' — how much of the initial

. display as text "    income level feeds into the growth rate."
    income level feeds into the growth rate.

. display as text "    When β > 0: convergence factor > 0, and the minus sign m
> eans"
    When β > 0: convergence factor > 0, and the minus sign means

. display as text "                higher initial income → lower growth (conver
> gence)"
                higher initial income → lower growth (convergence)

. display as text "    When β = 0: convergence factor = 0, no relationship"
    When β = 0: convergence factor = 0, no relationship

. display as text "    When β < 0: divergence"
    When β < 0: divergence

